enum.name: HermesResponseStatus
enum.summary: Statuses returned by Hermes, the Chrome OS daemon process which configures eSIM profiles a device's hardware.

int.label: kAllowed: Device can start a hotspot.
kDisallowedWiFiDownstreamNotSupported: Hotspot is not allowed because the downstream WiFi is not supported.
kDisallowedNoWiFiSecurityModes: Hotspot is not allowed because no WiFi security modes are supported
kDisallowedNoMobileData: Hotspot is not allowed because upstream cellular network is not connected.
kDisallowedReadinessCheckFail: Hotspot is not allowed because readiness check is failed, usually means the mobile data doesn't support hotspot.
kDisallowedByPolicy: Hotspot is not allowed because it is prohibited by the enterprise policy.
kReady: Readiness check pass and the current mobile data support hotspot.
kNotAllowed: Readiness check doesn't pass because the current mobile data doesn't support hotspot.
kUpstreamNetworkNotAvailable: Readiness check failed because upstream network is not connected.
kShillOperationFailed: Readiness check failed because of shill operation error.
kUnknownResult: Readiness check doesn't pass because of unknown result code.
kNotAllowedByCarrier: Readiness check doesn't pass because the carrier doesn't allow.
kNotAllowedOnFw: Readiness check doesn't pass because the outdated firmware.
kNotAllowedOnVariant: Readiness check doesn't pass because of the hardware limitations.
kNotAllowedUserNotEntitled: Readiness check doesn't pass because user's data plan is not entitled.
kAutoDisabled: Hotspot disabled due to fixed time of no connected device.
kInternalError: Hotspot disabled due to internal error.
kUserInitiated: Hotspot disabled due to user initiated operation.
kWifiEnabled: Hotspot disabled due to WiFi enabled.
kProhibitedByPolicy: Hotspot disabled due to policy restriction.
kUpstreamNetworkNotAvailable: Hotspot disabled due to no available upstream network.
kSuspended: Hotspot disabled due to device suspend.
kRestart: Hotspot disabled due to hotspot restart process.
kUpstreamNoInternet: Hotspot disabled due to upstream network has no Internet connectivity.
kDownstreamLinkDisconnect: Hotspot disabled due to downsteam link disconnected.
kDownstreamNetworkDisconnect: Hotspot disabled due to downstream network disconnected.
kStartTimeout: Failed to start tethering within given time
kUpstreamNotAvailable: Hotspot disabled due to upstream network not available.
kUnknownError: Hotspot disabled due to an unknown error.
kResourceBusy: Hotspot disabled due to concurrency resource conflict.
kFailedNotLogin: The operation failed because user is not login.
kFailedInvalidConfiguration: The operation failed because of invalid hotspot configuration.
kNotAllowed: The operation failed because it is not allowed.
kReadinessCheckFailure: The operation failed because tethering readiness check is failed.
kDisableWifiFailure: The operation failed because it failed to disable Wifi first.
kInvalidConfiguration: The operation failed because of invalid hotspot configuration.
kUpstreamNotAvailable: The operation failed because upstream network is not connected.
kNetworkSetupFailure: The operation failed because of network setup failure.
kDownstreamWifiFailure: The operation failed because of downstream WiFi operation failure.
kUpstreamFailure: The operation failed because of upstream network operation failure.
kShillOperationFailure: The operation failed because of shill operation error.
kUnknownFailure: The operation is failed because of unknown error.
kAlreadyFulfilled: The hotspot's current state is the same as the enable/disable operation requested.
kAborted: The enable hotspot operation has been aborted by the user.
kInvalid: The enable hotspot operation is invalid due to an ongoing disable operation.
kBusy: The enable hotspot operation failed due to an ongoing request.
kConcurrencyNotSupported: The enable hotspot operation failed due to concurrency conflict.
kOperationFailure: The enable hotspot operation failed internally.
